snippet: Teri McKeever has climbed through the ranks to become the first female head coach of the United States women’s swim team, but she considers herself a facilitator, not a trailblazer.
abstract: Teri McKeever has climbed through the ranks to become the first female head coach of the United States women’s swim team, but she considers herself a facilitator, not a trailblazer; she specializes in repairing broken psyches and pushing her swimmers to excellence in and out of the water.
lead_paragraph: Teri McKeever has climbed through the ranks to become the first female head coach of the United States women’s swim team, but she considers herself a facilitator, not a trailblazer.

headline.seo: Pinnacle for U.S. Swim Coach McKeever, but Don’t Call Her a Pioneer
headline.main: Now at the Pinnacle, an Uneasy Pioneer
headline.print_headline: Now at the Pinnacle, an Uneasy Pioneer
